{
  "text": "The Hip Outcome Score (HOS) is an instrument used to assess patients with hip disorders who are young, physically active, or both but who do not have severe degenerative abnormalities. Other hip assessment instruments do not address this population with the same degree of specificity [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
